thumb|1921 reprint of first edition king coal is a 1917 novel by upton sinclair that describes the poor working conditions in the coal mining industry in the western united states during the 1910s , from the perspective of a single protagonist , hal warner .

miner classics : 1917 's " king coal " by this author was to the mining industry what an earlier work had been to the meat - packing industry

